{% block form %}

  <h1 class="govuk-heading-l">
    You cannot get Attendance Allowance if you get the care component of DLA
  </h1>

  <p class="govuk-body">
    If you are already getting the care component of Disability Living Allowance (DLA),
    you are not eligible for Attendance Allowance.
  </p>

  <p class="govuk-body">
    <a class="govuk-link" target=”_blank” href="https://www.gov.uk/dla-disability-living-allowance-benefit">Find out more about DLA (opens in a new tab)</a>, including how to
    <a class="govuk-link" target=”_blank” href="https://www.gov.uk/dla-disability-living-allowance-benefit/your-DLA-claim">report a change to your care needs or circumstances (opens in a new tab)</a>
    if you only get the mobility component.
  </p>

  <p class="govuk-body">
    If you <a href="nationality" class="govuk-link">continue to apply for Attendance Allowance</a>,
    your existing benefits will be reviewed which may result in a change to what you currently get.
  </p>

